  <p>
      <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_gs1">GS1</xref>
 is an 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_organisation">ORGANISATION</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
      <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_gs1">GS1</xref>
 is a not-for-profit global standards 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_organisation">ORGANISATION</xref>
 that develops and maintains open standards to support industry. Using 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_gs1">GS1</xref>
 standards enables the universal unique identification throughout patient pathways and healthcare supply chains. Also, helping to facilitate 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/automatic_identification_and_data_capture.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Automatic_Identification_and_Data_Capture</xref>
 (
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/automatic_identification_and_data_capture.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">AIDC</xref>
), through the use of unique device identification (UDI).  </p>
  <p>
For further information on 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_gs1">GS1</xref>
, see the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_gs1">GS1</xref>
 website at: 
    <xref href="https://www.gs1uk.org/about-us"
            scope="external"
            format="html">About us</xref>
.  </p>

